					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6100619#post-4648918</guid>
				<title>Re: Easily my favorite Tale to date</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6100619/the-thing-at-the-bottom-of-my-dreams#post-4648918</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 16 May 2020 02:34:16 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>mlister</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3027978</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I easily appreciate the enthusiasm! It feels weird telling someone what they &quot;should&quot; be getting out of my work, atleast when they've got their own ideas going on, but I feel comfortable enough saying the answers to your questions are in Night 5's symbolism.</p> <p>I had <em>a</em> nascent idea for atleast one sequel, but my self-exile from the site hasn't helped matters. If you want to write something based off of your interpretations, I'd love and appreciate it. That's what No Canon is for after all. Just remember to get critique and the works, of course.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6100619#post-4648597</guid>
				<title>Easily my favorite Tale to date</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6100619/the-thing-at-the-bottom-of-my-dreams#post-4648597</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 15 May 2020 19:50:47 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Gladwin</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2101881</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Wait, do you mean to imply that the Library Serpent is Anantashesha is the Scarlet King, and is acting in opposition to SCP-3125 and/or the Fifthist Church&#8212; or are you implying that The Scarlet king is 3125 and/or The Fifth-thing, and that the Library Serpent opposes both&#8212; or that The Library Serpent is both the Scarlet King AND 3125/the Fifth-thing, and this force is either opposing something just as crazy huge, or staging a universal war against itself just to pretend to be a savior for a select few people??</p> <p>Also, what that hell makes &quot;you&quot; so special??? Who is this tale about?????</p> <p>This tale wrinkles my brain so hard.</p> <p>A person could right a whole cannon around this one tale. Maybe I will.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
