					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6100619#post-3831271</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6100619/the-thing-at-the-bottom-of-my-dreams#post-3831271</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sun, 10 Jun 2018 15:04:21 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>NatVoltaic</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2800867</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <blockquote> <p>It drops that last name on you with a certain weight, as if it expected you to recognize it. The message is lost on you, but it doesn't matter: you're not the intended audience.</p> </blockquote> <p>heh</p> <p>All in all this is a fun read with some good ol' eldritch shenanigans. Having what appears to be an apocalypse of many different gods is cool direction to go after Tufto's 001, and I'm looking forward to seeing where this is taken.</p> <p>+1</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
